@NODE INTRODUCTION "Introduction to DemoMaker"

			Introduction
			------------
	
	This program is made to create some simple demos/intros with:

	· A Logo shows in the begin of the Demo
	· A Mirror 
	· A Copper top and down
	· A rotating VectorCube (built-in)
	· A Starscroller (built-in)
	· A Big copper at the middle of the screen (built-in)
	· A Scrolling squares (built-in)
	· A scrolltext
	· And playing a module
	· A lots of effects,changed with the Effect Control Editor



@ENDNODE INTRODUCTION


@NODE REQUIREMENTS "What you need"

                               Requirements
                               ------------

	DemoMaker requires an Amiga with Kickstart/Workbench V2.0 or higher.

	DemoMaker has been tested on :

		A500 000/7 
		A500 000/14 with Blizzard Turbo Memory board 
		A4000 030/25 
		A4000 030/25 with Picasso IV Graphics card
		A4000 060/50 with Picasso IV Graphics card

	Minimum Requirements:
		Amiga with 68000, KS/WB 2.0, 1Mb ChipMem

@ENDNODE REQUIREMENTS


@NODE INSTALLATION "Installation"

                               Installation
                               ------------
		Just unpack the archive and put it where you want.
		Copy the contents in 'Font' drawer to your 'Fonts:'

@ENDNODE INSTALLATION


