@NODE DEMOMAKER "DemoMaker"
				What is DemoMaker ?
				-------------------

		DemoMaker is a program that you can make some demos/intros with.
		Here is an explanation of all gadgets:

 	· Load Module	-	Load a NT/PT compatible module
	· Load Logo	-	Load a logo, that displays in the begin of the demo
	· Load Anim	-	Load an IFF-Anim-brush, size 300x50, 50 frames
	· Edit Text	-	Brings up the TextEditor
	· Edit Copper	-	Brings up the CopperEditor

	· Options	-	Brings up the OptionsEditor
	· Options2	-	More options (Not in this version)
	· Clear Demo	-	Clear the demo
	· Info		-	Shows info about loaded objects etc...
	· About		-	Shows some info about the author
	
	· Play Module	-	Playing the module
	· Show Logo	-	Show the Logo in a window
	· Show Anim	-	Show the animation in a window
	· Show Cube	-	Show the 3D-Cube in a window
	· Empty		-	For future use

	· Restore	-	Restore all effects to default values
	· Load		-	Load a saved effectfile

	· Save Demo	-	Save the demo in a configfile, file extension: .Demo
	· Load Demo	-	Load a saved configfile of the demo

	· Processor	-	Shows what processor there is in the computer
	· Kickstart	-	Shows the Kickstart version
	· Graphics	-	Shows the graphic chipset

	· Status	-	Shows what DemoMaker is doing
	· Size		-	Shows the size of the demo

	· Test Demo	-	Test demo
	· Quit		-	Quit DemoMaker

@ENDNODE DEMOMAKER


